    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>si modo sunt Ma<lb break="no" n="3"/>nes sentiant spes vi<lb break="no" n="4"/>t<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> nostr<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> fueras <expan><abbr>nu</abbr><ex cert="low">n</ex></expan><lb break="no" n="5"/>c quis ubi iaceas indi<lb break="no" n="6"/>cat iste lapis <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Spurenni<lb break="no" n="7"/>us Herculanus frater et <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avia</ex></expan> Paula mater <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> Spuren<lb break="no" n="9"/>nio Rufo <expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>ucinatori</ex></expan> c<expan><ex>o</ex><abbr>h</abbr><ex>o</ex><abbr>r</abbr></expan>(tis) Mattia<lb break="no" n="10"/>corum militante <note>sic</note> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> XX <lb n="11"/>bene merenti posue<lb break="no" n="12"/>runt valete viatores
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Gefunden in einer antiken Nekropole. Oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes Darstellung eines galoppierenden Reiters (links) und eines Altars mit einer weiblichen Figur (rechts). (B): Škorpil - Škorpil; AE 1892; CIL III; CLE: Leseabweichungen.</p>
            </div>
